                <div class="taggedentity selected" reg="Putnam's and the Reader" xmlattrs="{&quot;LEVEL&quot;:&quot;JOURNAL&quot;,&quot;REG&quot;:&quot;Putnam's and the Reader&quot;,&quot;REF&quot;:&quot;&quot;}" xmltagname="TITLE" draggable="true" data-collection="">Putnam's and the Reader</div> 5 (October 1908-March 1909): 502-3.</div> 
            <div class="xmltag" xmlattrs="{}" xmltagname="AUTHORSUMMARY">
                <div class="xmltag" xmlattrs="{}" xmltagname="P">Ontario-born Sara Jeanette Duncan achieved considerable recognition for her many ironic novels and other writings that draw on her experiences in Canada, the US, England, and India.</div>
